赴任
ふにん<sup>２</sup>【赴任】 ﾛｰﾏ(funin)
〜する go to start a new job; start [leave] for one's new ⌐post [position].
▲新しく赴任してきた先生　a ⌐new [newly arrived] teacher
・彼はロンドン支店長として赴任した.　He went to take charge of the London branch.
▲赴任の途に上る　leave to take up a new position.
◧赴任先[地]　one's new place of appointment; one's new post.
赴任旅費　an allowance for taking up a new position.
